sub_title:
Connecting people, connecting Science and Society.
Head Dutch Research Agenda (NWA)
summary:
As head of the Dutch Research Agenda (NWA) at NWO, it is my passion to facilitate researchers and societal organisations to work together to answer research questions formulated by the societal community. Research funding  has, in my opinion, an essential role to play in stimulating the scientific and societal impact of science, as an intermediary between science, policymakers and societal stakeholders. I enjoy working with my team to work together in this, to try to reach our goals and to support my colleagues in their work pleasure and lifelong learning.

Expertise and skills: Skilled in Management, Science and Society and research funding, Public Health and SSH (Social sciences and Humanities). 

About the NWA:  The primary aim of the Dutch Research Agenda (NWA) is to build bridges between various scientific fields, between different types of research (fundamental, implied, practice-oriented) and between various national and international agendas.
